1://! `isolation=supervised` — the seccomp-notify supervisor tier
2://! (`docs/supervisor-design.md`).
3://!
4://! This is the security keystone: the first tier that may claim untrusted-code
5://! containment. Its defining property — implemented and tested here in phase A —
6://! is **fail-closed admission**: the claim is satisfiable only when *every*
7://! component probes green, and is otherwise **refused**, never downgraded to a
8://! weaker tier. A half-present stack is a refusal, not a "best-effort pass".
9://!
10://! Phase A (this module): the honest [`probe`], the pure syscall-decision model,
11://! and a fail-closed [`run`] (enforcement wiring is phase B). Because the full
12://! stack does not probe green on current hosts (WSL2/CI lack cgroup delegation
13://! and rootless nftables), the tier correctly refuses everywhere today.
